Step 6 — Confirm with token usage
Look at the usage line on the attachImage=true run. If vision genuinely processed the image, the prompt token count jumps noticeably versus the false run (images cost tokens). Same token count both times is another sign the image was ignored.
Step 7 — (Optional) Test your real screenshots
Once the synthetic probe passes, swap probe.jpg for an actual JPEG your capture produced — copy one out of the DB or call captureElementScreenshot once and write the buffer to disk. Then ask the model to describe what it sees. This catches a different failure: the plumbing is fine but your stored screenshots are empty/corrupt/blank.
